&lt;p&gt;Operations Support is currently undertaking a number of transformation projects covering vehicles, workshops, technology and make ready services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The roll out of make ready services is a priority for the Trust because of the benefits it brings to our patients, our staff and our underlying efficiency. The make ready service will be focused on efficiently providing a clean, safe and suitably stocked ambulance for our clinicians to look after our patients in.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Make Ready Group Lead role is key to supporting the roll-out of make ready and also through the ongoing operation of the service. You’ll be recruiting new team members, supporting and developing the existing team members, identifying new efficient systems, helping embed new technology and ways of working, and ensuring our make ready sites deliver the right service every day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will cover Cambridgeshire &amp; Peterborough.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
